HEADWORD: Pneumatometer
<hw>Pneu`ma*tom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Pneumato-</ets> + <ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>An instrument for measuring the amount of
force exerted by the lungs in respiration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

